reviews_data.review_text: I'am a life long Starbucks customer. I'am not sure how this store got 4.5 stars. I visit numerous Starbucks throughout the city. I was told at numerous locations, that the way I had requested my drink to be made was the correct way. The staff kept telling me I was wrong. I even ran into the district manger of that store at another Starbucks she managed. She told me I was correct. She asked me to give this store a chance. I did the very next day. Same result I heard a staff member tell another staff member , that she didn't have to make it the way I asked. Are you kidding me.  They're lazy  because that don't want to walk over and get hot water out of the right machine. I won't be attending this Starbucks again. If they keep this staff this location won't last trust me. If I could give this store zero stars I would. Most of the customers that come here mayn't know that other Starbucks have way better customer service. I mean I'am paying my money. I shouldn't have to argue with someone about what I want.

reviews_data.review_text: Siempre se pasa delicioso

My recent visit to Starbucks was ruined by an unbelievably rude transgender manager. From the moment I walked in, she/he barked orders at the staff loud enough for everyone to hear, creating a tense and uncomfortable vibe. When I approached the counter, I politely asked a simple question about the menu, and she cut me off mid-sentence with a snarky, “It’s all right there, figure it out.” I was stunned—customer service clearly isn’t His/her forte.I overheard Him/her dismiss another customer’s request with an eye-roll and a sarcastic comment, which just sealed the deal—this manager has no business being in charge. The staff seemed miserable under him/her, and honestly, I don’t blame them.
Starbucks is supposed to be a chill spot to grab a drink, not a battleground run by a power-tripping tyrant. Avoid this location unless you enjoy being treated like an inconvenience. Two stars, only because the drink wasn’t terrible.
